description:
While loop, as seen in many popular programming languages.

Takes an initital value, a function to produce a new value, and a function that determines whether to keep looping.

In effect, produces the following while loop:

while(continueWhile(init))
    init = body(init);
return init;

contents:
Loop While - Loops until a condition for a state is met, updating the state on each iteration.

Takes an initital value, a function to produce a new value, and a function that determines whether to keep looping.

In effect, produces the following while loop:

while(continueWhile(init))
    init = body(init);
return init;
